				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I normally just troll here but your post has inspired me to reply with some questions.
<br />

<br />
If GoD spells were named with Ancient in front of them, would you still feel ok about not getting these spells?  Does the simple title mean that much to you?
<br />

<br />
Now as far as the rightfully theirs by access, I have to contest that point as well.  So classes with spells should be allowed all spells from vendors with the exception of ancient spells?   
<br />

<br />
Well where does the difference come between say two mages, one that's bought platinum and then spells from the vendor or one that plays his character for a long time?  Pets don't scale with owners, with AAs and focuses there is some difference in DPS there. but not its not significant enough to represent the difference in quality time invested into the character.  There should be a difference somewhere I think, and this is part of it.
<br />

<br />
Now don't get me wrong I think they spells should be more readily available then they are now.  Perhaps an increased drop rate, make it available through a token earned at LDoN turned in somewhere in GoD, or simply take the NO DROP tag off it, or something like that.
<br />

<br />
I'm just failing to see why you are getting that upset about this.  You claim that there is not that much additional benefit from the spells...but you are really ranting about how you want them available.  In my personal opinion, spells shouldn't be looked at as something automatically granted to a class.  It's an item just like a weapon or a cloak.  Not a class ability like FD, backstab, taunt, etc.  And like other items, some items/spells are harder to obtain than others.  Enraging blow weapons aren't found on weapons commonly.  But a warrior could say it's a right to his class since his job is to tank.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
If you were wondering, I don't have any GoD spells, nor do I have Protection of Callinav, but I'm not complaining.  They are available, I have to just put time in it and not just plat.
<br />

<br />
Sorry if this all seems incoherant.  I'm posting this rather late.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
