			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">"Bazaar Mage" is defined as a Magician that gets his upgrades solely (aka Exclusively) from the Bazaar, 1 group encounters, and from LDoN (either from drops, or by purchasing with Adventure Points) and does little (if any) raiding. If a mage does any kind of regular or frequent raiding whatsoever for gear, then he is not a Bazaar Mage.
<br />

<br />
The issue with GoD spells is that, either spells should be a LOT more common for being No Drop, or should be droppable given the rarity. The problems is that they are both No Drop AND very rare.
<br />

<br />
Ancient spells are meant to separate the high end mage from the mid and lower end mage. Just as only the highest level players will see the best gear, only the highest end casters will see the best spells. Like gear, they should also be very rare.
<br />

<br />
Perhaps some spells should be vendor sold (like Elemental Siphon). But on the other hand, how many 61+ PoP spells are vendor sold? Maybe a couple of the lower end spells like Blessing of Reverence and Firebolt of Tallon, but ALL of the other spells are the result of killing a monster and looting something.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Xalmat Lunaire</a> (Mage) - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=816142" target="_blank" class="postlink">Venerable Eiyana Lunaire</a> (Cleric) -  <<a href="http://www.enshadowed.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Enshadowed</a>>
