			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">After all this time, happily lurking, and chuckling inwardly at some of the things I see on the tower here, I finally find myself compelled to retort a bit.  To equate time played, to the ability to gain top notch gear, is a sad, pathetic joke. I started playing a mage back before some of you folks in Kod'Taz and higher even heard of EQ. May '99 to be specific. Back when rogues were the most useless class in game, unable to even sneak and hide at the same time. 
<br />

<br />
To say that your time spent farming Time in some large guild is more valuable then my time spent attempting to get the Guild I have been in since day 1 to the Elementals, is a sad, sick joke. My time = Your time. End of story. Of course I feel upper tier raiding guilds should have the best stuff. it goes without saying. But GoD cuts everyone not at those levels off at the knees. We can't do a thing, and many people, myself included, would prefer that some of the earlier stuff be able to drop the spells, outside of Ancients, with at least some hope of us getting them, hopefully without having to save up 50K to buy it, were it no drop, from people who say "all we did is farm plat".  
<br />

<br />
Calling one group a bazaar mage, and the other a raiding mage misses the whole divergance within those groups. Am I a bazaar mage? No, I raided almost all of my gear, from my Grummus Ear, to my Cazic Robe, to the Staff of the Silent Star I am apt to whack things upside the head with. I don't have 6K mana, and 5K hps though, I sit at around 5K mana, and landed at 2300 hps on the dot. My gear is only *slightly* better than what someone could buy in bazaar, and I tend to have more FT than most, at 8.  I earned (note : earned) my DPoC, where it happily resides in my Orb of the Crimson Bull. 85 aa, again, hard earned, I can't earn this "easy" exp in PoFire and other places I hear tossed around here.. I tend to be in BoT, or gaining really, really crappy exp in normal LDoN, saving up for another copy of RGC, or maybe soon, my Mistmoore Robe, and an FT2 aug.   Hopefully I can get my Saryrn shield soon, if she decides to be nice and drop it for a change. 
<br />

<br />
So by this very defenition, I should be able to get these spells. After all, I am a raiding mage, am I not? But I can't. This is for raiding mages of a certain type of guild. One obviously, my guild is not, though hopefully, will be eventually. 
<br />

<br />
Personally, right now, all I want from GoD is my money back. I feel cheated. I was hoping, if anything, GoD might open a couple new targets for us to hit, that maybe the guilds in Time already would bypass, since they have more stuff to do. (stop killing TT please, you are already in Time, leave her alone so we can try.) Instead it opened up a whole lot of nothing. The Time guilds still come pounce on lower targets, laugh at the "shitty" loot, and once more take a path away from the raiders who have responsibilities as well. 
<br />

<br />
Stop talking like this is some prize you Timers "deserve". This old mage can still teach you a few tricks. Isn't that deserving enough? 
<br />

<br />
Arcale Vi`Cace
<br />
The Keepers
<br />
E'ci</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
