				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Did I just fall off of the mage tower and into Monkly-Business? 
<br />

<br />
It is also called you pissant upper tier fecks thinking you run stuff, especially these boards. Seems it is always the same ones. You all dislike the one mage that runs serverwide.magetower:fluffy (and I admit I hate him too) but you are turning out just like him. How is it you become just what you hate? It is this mentality that splits the class and NO REAL BALANCING can happen. We have long gotten away from what is good for the class and moved on to what's good for the raider or what's good for the soloer. Or what is good for the farmer. How about what is good for the CLASS. For crapsake it isn't just the raider or soloer that needs help. If you move past your freaking hole in the cloud where you sit there cross legged and meditate on wanting to be the best or wanting the best freaking gear, maybe you can buy a clue card. That card will probably tell you to get your head out of your butts and just concentrate on linear changes. Across the boards not just across the sects.
<br />

<br />
I will agree that to some extent *certain* spells should come from work. But things like Elemental Siphon or MS4 are not the ones I'd include. The nuke sure let that be from GoD only and the raiding there. Though you may not care but through time I have lost a ton of respect for some of the more premier mages on this board. I am disgusted and disgraced by how our class cannot even agree to one freaking change. Closed minded individuals all paranoid and crap, looking over their shoulder. "Oh nos, Joe Mage from a non-raid guild or from the Bazaar Association has the same spells as me WTF?!! I'm telling our mommy, SOE that I don't want this". Perhaps you folks at the top end that are complaining about how us non raiders are getting close should focus and just stick to getting class improvements. You can't balance stuff for raid mages exclusively without first balancing the class. It is times like this that I would not be heart broken to see them just get rid of this class.
<br />

<br />
You talk of putting in work to advance beyond the bazaar. All one mage can get from the bazaar that is even close to what you have at the high to very high end are spells. Your gear far surpasses what we can obtain in quests or trades so there is no real threat there. I have NO problem with that. Zero. Nada. I do have a problem with folks that have a history of having a spoiled brat mentality demanding they get something to make them stand out for accomplishing something. Man screw this crap. I know what topics interest me and I know the posting history of most. I will willfully just ignore posts that are not of the subject matter I am interested in. For those that suffered this I apologize. This just makes me sick to the very core. Players wanting class changes yet fighting in their own class.
<br />

<br />
Before I go, read this as posted at the very header of the forums:
<br />

<br />
