				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">where oh where have any of the "uber" people said the bazaar mages shouldn't get the same spells? (other than the ancients, which even a non uber can get ancient shock of the sun now)   i gave a respons to the hatred directed toward the ubers, but i didn't quite see where the ubers were bashing on the bazaar mages before that.
<br />

<br />
i see some random bitching that the "ubers" are getting spells an the rest aren't.. so sorry.. i have ele siphon and a guild that doesn't do trials 1-6 anymore.. unless magicly the other spells start dropping in kod taz + i won't be getting my spells at all most likely, unless they become droppable.   its the non ubers who will be getting rock and ms4, and you can also get siphon too..  now, if/when they go droppable, i'm still not gonna be able to buy the things because i have a total of 15 pp in my bank.. yes, i have a grand total of 15pp in my bank over all my chars combined..  why don't i have more?  well i had 45k but it poofed in the shared bank slot and the gm's wouldn't reimburse me, and now quite frankly, i don't have time to just farm stuff to sell/farm pp, and everything that drops for us is no drop for the most part.
<br />

<br />
and yeah, you'll find raid mages proposing raid mage fixes..  to be honest, mages int he 50's have it good (other than mana regen), its 62+ where we have real problems in my honest opinion.  - please note, i did 53-60 during the luclin  expasion and was a bazaar mage myself at that time, and i did it just fine... it wasn't that long ago, and yes i do remember it quite well.. oh the hours of killing guards in katta solo...   some ubers do reject the changes non ubers propose, some bazaar mages in return do the same for the changes the ubers present..  it works both ways people.  you are offended by the uber mages bashing you, and the uber mages are offended by you bashing them.   personally i tend to reject ideas i think are worhtless as a whole.. snare on pet.. this is almost totally worhtless for what a solo player would want, for a grp player it could be ok, but still the very very short duration and the unplannable casting of it by a pet would make it unreliable at best.  for raids it wouldn't do much of anything honestly. total sum - worthless idea imho.   this is just an example of how i really do think when i reject an idea...  i still LOVE to solo.. or would if it were possible for decent xp.  i group all the time (and yes, i do have problems finding groups, even in my "uber" state..)  and i raid 5 nights a week for roughly 5 hours a sitting... ( leaving very little time for regular xp btw..)i'm sure this is farily true of most raid mages... we spend our time largely raiding with a few off nights here and there to get xp, or xp for the hour or so we can play before/after raids and this should understandably color a raid mage's opinions.. they want stuff to help do what they do all the time.. for the non raider, you group/solo the majority so you want something that will help with that.  (and lets face it, the raiders have felt the grouping pinch in the last 2 expasions with ldon and GoD trials..)
<br />

<br />
oh and yeah.. ms4 is a raid pet.. i have no problems with it being so, PROVIDED THEY UPGRADE ALL OF OUR PETS SO OUR OLDER PETS BECOME VIABLE TOOLS FOR SOLOING/GROUPING.. which is what all mages support.   our pets are specialized like that.. whats wrong with having a pet that is more specialized to raiding?  - note, i was in beta and did NOT ask for ms4 to be a raid pet.. i wanted it to be a soloing pet honestly and did give feedback in that regard..  we have 5 pets to choose from.. ms4 shouldn't be the best pet for all situations, neither should air (although honestly its just about the only one i mem ever) or water, or earth.. they each do different things for different situations.. ms4 being a raid pet with high dmg hits and the proc also makes it a damn nice group pet.. in groups you don't have to worry about correct position like water pet, but you do more dmg than air and still get a stun.. and that one absorption proc helps with enrage - which i'm sure many many mages have been a little slow to back a pet off of an enraged mob before and seen the hp just drop fast..<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99608" target="_blank" class="postlink">Daetien Beyazid</a> 
